# User Guide

This guide covers the main features available in your application.

## Authentication

The application uses **Keycloak** for authentication. Login is handled via the OAuth2 Authorization Code flow with PKCE.

- Click **Login** to be redirected to Keycloak
- After successful authentication you are redirected back to the application with an active session
- Click **Logout** to destroy the session and be redirected to the Keycloak logout page
- Sessions expire after **24 hours** of inactivity

## Access Control

Access control is managed via **Casbin** with a role-based model (RBAC).

- Permissions are stored in the `ac_rules` table and managed at `/admin/ac-rules`
- Each permission is a combination of **role**, **resource**, and **action** (`create`, `read`, `update`, `delete`)
- Users are assigned roles via the `g` (grouping) policy type

**Built-in roles:**

| Role | Description |
|---|---|
| `superadmin` | Full access to everything, bypasses all policy checks |
| `__LOGGEDUSER__` | Any authenticated user |
| `__GUEST__` | Unauthenticated user |

