## Search Index Management

The search index management interface at `/admin/search-reindex` allows you to manage search indexes per entity:

| Action | Description |
|---|---|
| **Reindex** | Create the index if needed, then index all records |
| **Flush** | Remove all records from the index, keeping the structure |
| **Delete index** | Permanently remove the index |

Bulk operations are available via checkbox selection.
<%_  } _%>

## API Documentation

An interactive API documentation interface is available at `/support/api-docs`, powered by Swagger UI and an OpenAPI 3.0 specification.

**Authenticating in Swagger UI:**

- **Bearer token** — paste a valid JWT in the Authorize dialog
- **OAuth2** — click Authorize, select OAuth2, and log in via Keycloak

**For machine-to-machine integrations**, use the Client Credentials flow to obtain a token directly from Keycloak, then pass it as a `Bearer` header in all API calls.
